@node Main "gcc.guide"
@next "G++ and GCC"

Introduction
************

This manual documents how to use the GNU compilers, as well as their
features and incompatibilities, and how to report bugs.  It corresponds
to GCC version 3.4.0.  The internals of the GNU compilers, including
how to port them to new targets and some information about how to write
front ends for new languages, are documented in a separate manual.  See
@{"gccint.guide/Introduction" link "gccint.guide/Main"}.


 @{" G++ and GCC    " link "G++ and GCC"}  You can compile C or C++ programs.
 @{" Standards      " link "Standards"}  Language standards supported by GCC.
 @{" Invoking GCC   " link "Invoking GCC"}  Command options supported by @{b}gcc@{ub}.
 @{" C Implementation " link "C Implementation"}  How GCC implements the ISO C specification.
 @{" C Extensions   " link "C Extensions"}  GNU extensions to the C language family.
 @{" C++ Extensions " link "C++ Extensions"}  GNU extensions to the C++ language.
 @{" Objective-C    " link "Objective-C"}  GNU Objective-C runtime features.
 @{" Compatibility  " link "Compatibility"}  Binary Compatibility
 @{" Gcov           " link "Gcov"}  @{b}gcov@{ub}---a test coverage program.
 @{" Trouble        " link "Trouble"}  If you have trouble using GCC.
 @{" Bugs           " link "Bugs"}  How, why and where to report bugs.
 @{" Service        " link "Service"}  How to find suppliers of support for GCC.
 @{" Contributing   " link "Contributing"}  How to contribute to testing and developing GCC.

 @{" Funding        " link "Funding"}  How to help assure funding for free software.
